  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A Requirement node mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis output comparison; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as a literature-review of published hemolysis correlations and prior CFD studies. The narrative frames the literature survey as complementary evidence, but the structured activityType disagrees with requiredVerificationMethod, breaking the inference link (W-AR-03).",
