    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The hemolysis output comparison credibility factor was assessed as satisfied based on agreement between CFD predictions and the envelope of values reported across 34 peer-reviewed publications in the literature review. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirmed P95 NIH remains below the clinical threshold. The literature survey provides comprehensive coverage of hemolysis behaviour in centrifugal blood pumps and is considered adequate supporting evidence. All other assessed factors show gaps but are judged acceptable given the conservative uncertainty margins demonstrated by the Monte Carlo analysis.",
